# Medallion — what's in each layer

The exam tests: read a description → name the layer.

## Bronze — raw, append-only, replayable

- One table per source; schema mirrors source (nested OK)
- Strings + nulls allowed; quality **NOT** enforced — the **audit copy**

## Silver — cleaned, conformed, deduplicated

- **Same grain** as bronze (one row per event); types pinned, nulls dropped
- Conformed FKs; quality **enforced** (expectations / `CHECK`)

## Gold — business-ready, aggregated, served

- Star schema or wide rollup; pre-aggregated; one row per **entity**
- Permissions tightest — analysts / ML join here

**Rule:** many narrow gold tables from the **same** silver — not one giant table.
